# Python Style

- Python 3.12+. Use `type` statement for type aliases. Use `X | None` not `Optional[X]`.
- All functions have return type annotations. All parameters have type annotations.
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in every file.
- Pydantic BaseModel for data classes. `@dataclass` only for internal-only containers.
- Use `structlog.get_logger()` not `logging.getLogger()`.
- Prefer explicit imports. No `from module import *`.
- Functions that call LLMs are always `async`. Functions that do CPU work are sync.
- Error handling: custom exception hierarchy rooted at `AnvilError`. Never bare `except:`.
- Docstrings: one-line summary for simple functions. Google style for complex ones.
- f-strings for string formatting. Never `.format()` or `%`.
